inn1.comm: a bit of swing into the pads first up, tucked towards midwicket by Jamshed
length ball on off stump, solidly defended towards mid-off, Jamshed sprints down the ground, Hafeez stays his ground, no trouble there as Jamshed realises early enough that there no run
on the pads, not much movement, helped down towards fine leg
angling int towards the off stump, no repeat of that dramatic Hafeez bowled dismissal this time, defended to the leg side by Hafeez
thick outside edge as Hafeez pokes at the ball outside off stump, that runs away past the second slip, where Ashwin dives in vain, third man is not too fine, so that's a boundary
pitched up, blocked towards mid-on, no dramatic movement in that over
back of a length ball on leg stump, 141kph, swings in a little, defended to the leg side
outside off this time, 139.8kph, left alone by Jamshed
that stayed low, 138kph from Dinda, but doesn't carry through to Dhoni much above his knee height, that was outside off and another leave from Jamshed
on the pads, clipped away towards deep square leg for a couple
short ball from Dinda, that was way over the batsman's head, 143kph from Dinda, rightly called a wide
back of a length and on the pads, tucked to square leg, there's a fielder fairly close in there, prevents the single
short and down the leg side, Dinda grunts as he bowls that one, 142 kph from him, not much use as that is called a wide
better from Dinda, back of a length and on off stump, defended back towards the bowler

length ball outside off, Hafeez reaches forward and drives that towards deep backward point, an elegant shot from Hafeez, they decide to come back for the second, Hafeez has to dive to get bak in time
plenty of work here for Ishant, after running to his right on the previous ball, this time he has to sprint and slide to his left, it was an outside edge from Hafeez towards third man
defended off the front foot towards cover, no movement for Bhuvneshwar
another outside edge, Hafeez looking to drive well away from his body, flies past Ashwin at gully this time, can't call that a chance, was too wide

there's a theory that Bhuvneshwar won't cause much problems to batsmen when the ball isn't snaking around, he's causing plenty of trouble to Hafeez this over though, getting the ball to bounce and Hafeez misses as he looks to play that to point
solid defence to the off side to end the over, a good one fron Bhuvneshwar
pitched up and outside off, slashed towards backward point
on the pads, flicked over Ashwin at square leg, too quick and too high for Ashwin, who didn't even jump when that came towards him
defended by Jamshed to the off side
length ball well outside off, guided towards deep backward point by Jamshed, nicely done there by the batsman
there's the Dinda bouncer again, 143kph, third bouncer and the third wide
defended towards point from the crease, a quick single is pinched as there is a slight midfield, Hafeez gestures to Jamshed asking to him to call clearly
pitched up and on off stump, defended towards the bowler
walks across the stumps and looks to whip the ball towards midwicket, misses and is struck on the pads well outside off
pretty close to off stump, Hafeez confident enough to leave, though the memory of his dismissal to an inswinger in the previous match will be fresh
far too wide from Bhuvneshwar, easy put away for Hafeez, slaps it towards the point boundary, it's a supremely quick outfield here
looks to drive on the up through cover, takes a couple of paces down the track as hetries to play that, inside-edges it to the leg side for a single
pitched up and that is defended back towards the bowler
stays low and that hits very low on the bat as Jamshed stays back and defends towards the bowler
Ishant begins with a short of length ball outside off, a mistimed slap towards cover
pitched up and on the pads, defended towards the bowler
Hafeez having trouble with the bounce here, Ishant gets it to rear up a touch, Hafeez again trying an extravagant drive, off the back foot and away from his body, misses
extra bounce once more, Hafeez takes the bottom and off the bat as  he plays that, hitting high on the bat, on the sponsors' logo
length from Ishant, slants in towards Hafeez, who works that towards mid-on
pitched up and wide, Hafeez drives that towards deep backward point, Dinda races across to cut that off, to the delight of his home crowd
thick outside edge towards third man, where Dinda is scampering around once more, dives to stop that from reaching the rope. Has he stopped that? nope, he hasn't
back of a length ball on the pads, poor delivery from Bhuvneshwar, easy glance down to fine leg for four, two boundaries to start the over then
fuller and outside off, Jamshed can't time it as he looks to drive through the overs
better timing this time as he slashes it towards point, can't beat the fielder
shortish ball angling across, Jamshed bends his knees as he easily gets under that one
another thick outside edge, past the slips and down to Dinda at third man
lovely shot from Hafeez, stays in the crease and caresses that towards the point boundary, top shot that
short of length and outside off, left alone by Hafeez, carries through very low to Dhoni
this one carries through at shoulder height to Dhoni, back of a length ball outside off, Hafeez leaves it alone
another thick outside edge as he drives it behind backward point, Hafeez zips back for the second, he has no moved on to 26 off 24, though he hasn't looked entirely comfortable in the middle
slants in towards middle, tucked towards the leg side by Hafeez
pitched up, on middle and leg stump, whipped towards deep backward square leg
a half-volley on the pads, dismissed by Hafeez, a lovely on-drive sends the ball racing away for four
beaten outside off, that one carries straight on outside off, Hafeez looks to drive and misses, Hafeez sticks his tongue out after missing that one
looks to flick that, plays it uppishly, just over midwicket , it was short of a length ball on middle stump, two more to Hafeez
length and just outside off, defended off the front foot towards cover
terrific drive from Hafeez, leans across and crashes that through the covers for four, nothing happening here for India's quick bowlers
back of a length ball outside off, Hafeez shoulders arms
swing and a miss outside off, Jamshed looks to chop a back of length ball outside off and he misses
a thick inside egde this time as Jamshed looks to block an offstump ball off the back foot, sends the ball towards deep square leg
short of length ball just outside off, defended by Hafeez
length ball outside off, defended off the front foot towards cover
length ball on off stump, more defence from Hafeez
length ball outside off, Hafeez shoulders arms to that one, end of the Powerplay, Pakistan will be delighted with how that went
length ball from round the stump, blocked off the front foot to the off side, good bounce there
a thick outside edge, as Jamshed looks to play that to the leg side, flighted and it curves in, takes the edge and down to third man, it is a lightning outfield here
more solid defence this time from Jamshed
length ball on the pads, not turn there, whipped towards deep square leg
pitched up and outside off, worked towards midwicket off the front foot
punched towards cover this time, a good first over from Ashwin
full and well outside off, driven towards deep point for a single
short of length and outside off, Hafeez swishes at it and misses once more, there's been several of those in Hafeez's innings, once again the extra bounce does him in
135kph from Ishant, a short of length ball outside off, Hafeez skips down the track and slaps that towards midwicket
wrong line from Ishant, down the leg side, easily helped along, sends it wide of fine leg for four, poor ball that
Jamshed is surprised by that one, looked to defend it but ends up almost punching that short of length ball back to the bowler, drops short
length ball outside off, poked towards cover off the front foot
length ball from over the wicket, defended off the front foot to the leg side
superb shot from Hafeez, waits on the back foot and gracefully sends the ball towards deep backward point
shovels this from well outside off towards deep square leg, Kohli dives near the rope to stop that one
again Hafeez looking good as he slices the ball off the back foot towards deep point
length ball from round the wicket, no turn on offer, defended down the track
full ball around off, defended off the front foot
back of a length ball angling away, chopped towards sweeper cover
full and outside off, Hafeez reaches across and drives it to cover
126kph, short from Bhuvneshwar, at his pace and on this pitch against set batsmen, not going to trouble much, Hafeez is terrific on the pull, he punishes that to the midwicket boundary
pushed towards cover this time
delicate from Jamshed, need plenty of confidence to play this one, just waits for the ball to arrive outside off and dabs it wide of the keeper for four, realises there are no slips
clipped off the pads towards midwicket for a single
pitched up from round the wicket, driven along the ground to long-on, Pakistan cruising here
more flight this time, spinning away just a little, forward defensive from Jamshed
more watchful batting from Jamshed, blocks it to the off side

nearly a wicket there, Jamshed looks to power the ball through cover, edges it towards backward point, Kohli makes a terrific effort there to take that as it loops towards him, gets his fingers on it but that was dying on him, Ashwin applauds the effort
defended by Jamshed
pushed to long-off for a single
his first ball is muscled past mid-on for four, not the prettiest of strokes but mighty effetcive
defended to the off side
pushed towards deep point for a single
on the pads, flicked towards deep square leg for a single that brings up Hafeez's half-century
poor stuff this from Raina, drops it short and that sits up for Jamshed, who obliges by mowing it to midwicket
fired in flatter, on off stump defended back to the bowler
flighted and full, on middle stump, bowling round the wicket, defended to the leg side
Hafeez jumps down the track, Ashwin bowls it shorter, Hafeez looks to slam that down the ground, inside-edge towards mid-on
that slides straight on, Jamshed blocks off the back foot
another outside edge, as Ashwin gets the ball to grip and turn, it falls short of Sehwag at first slip, Pakistan's 100 comes up
not much room outside off, Hafeez still manages to dab that towards third man
starts with a flat delivery that spins away, defended from the crease t othe off side
full ball on the pads, squeezed towards midwicket
Jadeja getting some turn here, pitching on a length and moving towards off, defended to the leg side
looks to force the ball through the off side, gets it off the inside-half of the bat
worked to midwicket, where Raina fields, he slips as he gets up to throw
cheekily played just past slip for four to third man, had been only two runs off the first five balls, but the boundary makes it six off the over
full and on the pads, to midwicket for a single
waits on the back foot and guides the ball towards point for a single
spins in instead of away as Jamshed expects, zips off the track and that is a thick inside-edge on to the pads
length ball outside off, defended off the front foot towards extra cover
tossed up and on the pads, Jamshed has hammered that to wide long-on for four to bring up his half-century in style
length ball bowled from a little round-arm action, watchfully defended
on the pads, helped towards square leg for a single
spins in towards the off stump, eased towards long-on
pitched up, on middle and leg, defended to the bowler
on middle and leg, tucked towards square leg
shimmies down the track and eases the ball to long-on, Pakistan scoring without needing to take risks here
quicker from Jadeja, batsman stays on the back foot and defends
Ashwin's been bowling well today, just outside off, slapped towards point
from round the wicket, full ball outside leg stump, looks to sweep and is struck on the pads
whipped towards midwicket for another single
worked to midwicket, Hafeez wanted one, Jamshed didn't after taking a couple of steps forward, bit of confusion but Hafeez turns back in time

pushed towards cover this time, Jamshed starts sprinting though it is straight at the fielder, there was no single there, Hafeez knew that and didn't budge, Jamshed turns back and dives to beat the throw, Raina's weak throw hits Jamshed near the boot
careful defence down the track
pitched up, defended towards extra cover

horrible terrible nearly got a wicket, full ball down the leg side, Hafeez looks to sweep and top-edges that towards fine leg, Dinda makes an awkward dive to try haul that, more like a long jumper than a fielder, could have hurt himself badly there

another sweep, another top edge, this time it swirls towards deep square leg, Gambhir has plenty of ground to make, he races to his left but can't get there in time, he makes a feeble one-handed snatch at the last moment, doesn't stick
defended towards cover this time
eased towards long-on for a single
sensible push towards long-off for a single
tucks that length ball from middle stump, plays it with soft hands and places it past square leg to get enough time to sprint back the second
after the delicate shot off the first ball, shows off his power this time, jumps down and launches that over mid-off for four
swept towards square leg for a single
Jamshed this time, terrific batting from Pakistan here, a paddle sweep for four, not much power from Jamshed but spot-on placement
another sweep, a controlled one behind square leg
defended off the back foot to the left of the bowler
whipped towards long-on for a single
was there an edge there? Dhoni has put it down after Hafeez looked to cut that one, flighted ball from Jadeja
pushed to cover by Hafeez

India get the breakthrough, it's Jadeja who gets the wicket, Hafeez was in trouble playing the sweep in the previous over against Jadeja as well, this time he doesn't make contact at all and the middle stump is on the ground
length ball on off stump, Azhar Ali defends to the off side off the front foot
short of length and angling across, 135kph, slapped towards deep point
length ball pitched up, driven to the right of the bowler
134.6kph, length ball angling in towards middle, punched and reaches the bowler on the bounce, Dinda snatches at the ball
the Dinda bouncer finally comes good, 139kph, just outside off has the new batsmen fending at it, off the gloves and wide of slip, terrific delivery that
pitches it up this time outside off, Azhar Ali is beaten by that one
shortish from Dinda, 138kph, Azhar Ali is hopping as he tucks that towards square leg
gets well forward and defends to the off side
eased to long-off for a single
spins in towards off stump, clipped towards midwicket
on the pads, helped along to long leg for a single
pitched up and on off stump, skidding straight on, defended off the frontfoot

and Pakistan have lost a second, Azhar Ali is walking back, there was initially a huge lbw appeal as Ali looked to sweep that, got some glove on it and looked to be outside off as well, so Bowden turned it down, the ball rolled in the direction of square leg , not too far from the stumps, Ali wanted a single, Dhoni quickly moved to field, the batsman was stranded mid-pitch as Jamshed rightly knew there was no single, Sehwag had moved up to the stumps, Dhoni underarms it to Sehwag, and India have a second wicket
firmly struck towards cover point
short of length and outside off, driven towards cover

shot! one of the best of the day, the typical Dinda short ball, Jamshed waits for it and pulls that in front of square for six, as authoritative as they come, hit quite low on the bat but still easily cleared the rope
worked towards point by Jamshed
punched off the back foot towards cover
short of length ball just outside off, guided towards backward point
stretches forward and pushes the ball towards cover
worked towards midwicket for a single
length ball spins towards leg stump, pushed to midwicket

nearly a run-out there, Jamshed punches the ball back towards the bowler, Jadeja does well to get a hand on it and flick it on the stumps, Younis had taken a few steps out of the crease but he gets back just in time
whipped towards square leg for a single
spins away from Younis, played towards short third man
looking for a flamboyant drive through the off side, that was quite wide, but Jamshed misses
well outside off again, any farther from the stumps and that will be called a wide, left alone by Jamshed
pitched up and just outside off, crashed through extra cover, powerfully hit, even Raina who is one of the best Indian fielders, couldn't stop that
worked in front of square leg for a single
length ball just outside off, defended back towards the bowler
beaten outside off as Younis searches for the ball, it was back of a length and didn't move much
length ball just outside off stump, nudged towards square leg
driven towards long-off by Younis
huge lbw appeal, turned down by Billy Bowden, Jadeja gets that flighted ball to spin in but was probably going to miss leg stump, good call
punched towards long-on for a single
down to short fine leg for another single to end the over
Younis wafts outside off, straightens a touch off the pitch, Younis beaten
worked to backward point for a single
this time is is Jamshed who is fishing outside off, the angle beats the bat, Jamshed isn't a big fan of footwork, just pokes at it and misses
length ball outside off, mistimed back to the bowler
slower ball form Ishant, 111kph, short of length ball just outside off, defended towards cover, good over this from Ishant
punched off the back foot towards cover, just one off the over
driven towards long-off for a single
jumps down the track and eases the ball towards long-on
length ball is defended to the off side
a leading edge almost pops back to the bowler, Pakistan getting themselves in a bit of bother here, though the score is a very healthy 166/2
driven towards long-on for a risk-free single
single to long-off this time
short and outside off, too high to be legal, well over the batsman's head
defended off the front foot towards the off side
pushed towards mid-on for a single
close to off stump, Younis chops it towards point
works it towards sweeper cover for a single
looks to hammer that one from outside off, he misses, a sign of impatience from Jamshed, a sign of how India have pulled things back in the last few overs
slower one outside off, guided down to third man for a single
pitched up and outside off, slapped towards cover point, two fielders in that area, very tough to get it past them
very close to off stump, opens the face to guide it towards third man
short of length ball on off stump, clipped towards midwicket
shortish ball outside off, looked to carve it through the off side, a bit of a top edge, on the bounce to third man
pitched up and outside off, driven towards sweeper cover
short of length ball just outside off, a wristy shot send the ball to midwicket, a tight single is taken
length ball outside off, punched down the ground for one
flicked through square leg

loud appeal and given, Younis trapped lbw on the sweep, but there was a huge inside edge before the ball struck the pad in front of middle, what a shocker, what an absolute shocker from umpire Kulkarni, there has to be some way to weed these out of the game, DRS or no DRS
he is down for the sweep outside off stump very early, but cannot connect in the end
off the mark with a single to the leg side
tucked off the pad past midwicket, Rohit is on the field, he gives chase, slides and keeps them to one
tossed up in from round the stumps, pushed towards mid on
stays in the crease, the length ball skids on outside off, stabbed away towards point
stops in the delivery stride, bowls it into the pads, worked square
slapped away straight to extra cover, not timing it well
pushes forward to a flighted ball, thick inside edge towards square leg

that looked close, loud, long appeal, and umpire Bowden gives it, nothing wrong with the decision, Misbah looking to work it with the spin to the leg side, misses the line of the offbreak, and is hit in front of middle and off, some comeback this from India, they had no answers against Hafeez and Jamshed
defended tightly from the crease, length ball angled in
pitched up outside off, left alone
hops to a back of a length ball, and guides it wide of third man, did not get up as much as he was expecting, had to adjust
full and across the left-hander, he cannot get bat to it
tight over, Pakistan cannot afford to go hard in the Powerplay with all those wickets falling, pushed to short extra cover
tossed up full toss eased down to long on
angled in from round the stumps, defended off the front foot, slip in place

more trouble for Pakistan? Jamshed had been smashing them through extra cover earlier, this time he mistimes a drive wide of mid off, Kohli hits the non-striker's stumps direct, Jamshed has just made it
goes back and across in the crease, and works it to the leg side
lunges forward and pushes a full one to short midwicket
that has kept low, from a pitched-up length, getting more difficult now, as far as batting goes, stabbed into the off side
back of a length ball just outside off, guided towards short third man
gets out of the rut with a straight six, that was back of a length, Jamsheddoesn't move his feet much but clouts that over the bowler's head to move to 96
that stayed a bit low, just outside off, Jamshed stayed
on the pads, a well-timed flick sends the ball towards deep midwicket, they race back for the second
defended towards midwicket after going well back in the crease
Jamshed moves to 99, another ball on leg stump, clipped towards deep backward square leg
Ashwin bowls it on a length, defended off the front foot to the off side
punched towards cover, he remains on 99
there's the century, his third in a row against India, thumped that between the bowler and mid-off, it was played uppishly as well, but with plenty of power, Jamshed celebratory with a fist pump
down the leg side for a couple of wides
worked towards midwicket, Shoaib wanted a single but Jamshed sends him back
dispatched towards deep midwicket for two more
pitched up and just outside off, defended towards point
driven towards long-off for a single
back of a length ball outside off, defended towards cover
a yorker on middle stump, dug out to the left of Dhoni for a single

looks to cut an outside off delivery, there's an edge down towards third man, Shoaib wanted the second, he was going to the danger end, he was wheeling away, Jamshed didn't want the second, Shoaib has to turn back, Jamshed's looking like an impressive batsmen, but he needs to work on his running between the wickets
another yorker from Bhuvneshwar, squeezed out to the off side
length ball, slower one outside off, stays low and Shoaib misses it as he looks to work it to third man

stumped! Jamshed was several yards down the track to try force the ball, he misses it and is well out, but Dhoni misses it as well, he doesn't collect it cleanly, but he is fortunate to get a second chance as the ball lobs up off his gloves, taps it on to the stumps and Jamshed will have to be satisfied with 106 today
big turn for Jadeja there, a tricky first ball for Kamran, beaten as he plays down the wrong line

Jadeja uis having a great time out there, another wicket for him, Kamrna Akmal has to go for a duck as he edges the ball to slip, not often that you see slip at this stage of the innings, Jadeja's team-mates are ruffling his hair in celebration, Pakistan had looked well on course for 300 not too long ago, they'll have to settle for less now
length ball just outside off, defended off the front foot
flatter delivery just outside off, Gul gets forward and defends it
a double-wicket maiden from Jadeja as the last ball is blocked to the leg side
one of the ugliest shots you will see, drops it short, too short, Malik heaves it to the midwicket boundary, almost falling over as he plays that shot
quicker and outside off, fuller as well, defended off the back foot
quicker one again, Malik looks to cut it but it stays low and gets beaten
worked towards midwicket off the back foot, Malik gets two more
length ball heading for off stump, defended back towards the bowler
short of length ball well outside off, guided down to third man
final over from Jadeja, length ball is blocked back to the bowler
another of those languid drives from Gul, towards cover
towards square leg for a single
pitched up, on off stump, defended towards the bowler
Gul can hit sixes, he's shown that before, and he shows the packed house at the Eden Gardens as well, times it perfectly as he sweeps that over the midwicket boundary
reverts to careful forward defence, Jadeja finishes with 3 for 41
short of length ball just outside off, guided down to third man
just outside off, squeezed down towards third man
pitched up and that is driven crisply towards cover
once more the ball stays low, and it take an eternity to reach Malik, back-of-the-hand slower ball from Dinda, Malik looks to cut but that sneaks under
a bit of width, Malik chops it towards cover point, Jadeja is the fielder, a direct hit would have caught Gul well short, Gul had given up in fact, he misses though
another back-of-the-hand slower ball, 104.9kph, full and on the pads, Gul looks to work it towards the leg side, but misses, a mild lbw appeal
slower one from Bhuvneshwar, driven towards sweeper cover
short of length ball well wide of offstump, thick edge towards third man
pitched up and that is another solid Malik drive that fetches him no runs, this was towards extra cover
another ugly shot from Malik, looking to scythe to midwicket from well outside off, can't connect properly, the ball lobs beyond mid-on
steers there down to third man for a single
a yorker outside off, jammed towards gully for a single
Ishant slower ball gets the wicket, 107kph, pitched up and just outside off, Malik looks to launch that over the in-field, can only chip it as far as cover, Pakistan lose their seventh
short ball outside off, 135.4kph, slapped towards deep point
another fluid drive towards cover, placement not great though, so no run
defended back towards the bowler
short of length ball sliding on to the pads, helped towards short fine leg

did that slip out of Ishant's hand, a high full toss down the leg side, helped down to fine leg for four, the batsman saw that come well above knee-height and didn't look to smash it, just deflected it to the rope, Ishant has his hand up in apology
what a shot that is, Ajmal paddle-scoops to the fine leg boundary, clever batting that, there was no one in the deep there
slow ball outside off, slapped towards backward point
full ball just outside off, driven towards extra cover
a bouncer outside off, Ajmal happy to see it through to the kepeer
short ball, 130.7kph, Ajmal goes for the pull,and top-edges it, it swirls towards Sehwag at midwicket, easy catch, Pakistan eight down, can they last the full 50?
short of length ball outside off, steered down to third man for a single, Gul looking at ease in the middle
Ishant gets another, Gul was looking to send that towards midwicket, it was not short enough for the swipe which Gul favours, the ball sneaks under the bat and hits the top of off
pitched up and was heading for middle, Irfan punches it towards mid-off
it's all over, Mohammad Irfan loses his middle stump, that hits the middle of middle, Irfan doesn't move his feet an inch, he looks to defend but misses the ball and is bowled for 0

inn2.comm: Mohammad Irfan starts with a back of a length delivery that is jabbed towards point by Gambhir
Irfan had his hands up in celebration there, he thought he had Sehwag bowled, it was just outside off, Sehwag was going for the cut, a bottom-edge that whizzes past the stumps
on the pads, 135.8kph, tucked towards square leg
spearing down the leg side, Gambhir looks to glance it but it is off the thigh pad and towards fine leg for four leg-byes
just outside off, 140.9kph, the typical extra bounce for Mohammad Irfan, short of a length ball rears up outside off, Gambhir shoulders arms

serious confusion between Sehwag and Gambhir, nearly resulted in a run-out, Gambhir was first cramped up by a delivery that angled in towards him, he managed to get it away towards point, Sehwag didn't want a single, but Gambhir was dashing for a run, sent back and Gambhir makes it back in time
Junaid, such a terror with the new ball in the previous game, gets the ball to swing in, pitching outside leg so the loud lbw appeal is turned down
on the pads once more, slants in again, struck on the pads
short of length ball, 130.5kph, just outside off, defended towards point
down the leg side, swinging past the pads and Kamran Akmal has to dive to collect the ball, he can't and they pinch an extra run
outside off and moving away, Gambhir shoulders arms
pitching on a length well outside off, Gambhir looks to drive, but mistimes towards the bowler
Gambhir nibbles at it outside off, luckily for him he doesn't get bat on it, superb first over from Junaid
short of length ball, Sehwag gets close to the line of the ball and pushes it towards cover
shorter and just outside off, Sehwag chops it off the back foot towards point, 'No, no, no,' he calls to Gambhir
short of length ball just outside off, cracking stroke from Sehwag sends the ball racing through cover for four, played with both feet in the air
another powerful shot from Sehwag, shifts his weight to the back foot and carves it towards cover where Azhar Ali fields
a full toss outside off, 140kph, Sehwag looks to dig it out towards the off side, he can't get bat on it
141kph from Irfan, Sehwag stays on the back foot and steers the ball towards backward point, he thinks about a single before Gambhir sends him back
Junaid gets this one to curve in, he has been getting the ball to generally move away so far, Gambhir leaves this one and it isn't too far away from the off stump
bit of width for Gambhir, he lashes that off the back foot behind point for four, Mohammad Irfan runs across and dives but this outfield is superfast

an absolute pearler from Junaid, much too good for Gambhir, who was looking to work that form outside off towards midwicket, it was a sensational delivery, swinging in and then seaming away, Gambhir beaten all ends up
plays this straight this time, towards mid-on for a single
length ball is punched towards mid-on
gets this one to swerve away from Sehwag, who chases it but can't get bat on that 139kph delivery, another testing over from Junaid comes to an end
Gambhir french-cuts this towards fine leg, he jumped to try get on top of the bounce and defend to the leg side, once more Irfan was anticipating a wicket, Gambhir shadow-practises leaving the ball
punched firmly but straight at the fielder at mid-off
short of length outside off, Sehwag shows why he is so dangerous, moves closer to the line of the delivery and murders that behind point, a powerful cut for four

pitched up this time, Sehwag opens the face and guides the ball towards point, Hafeez fumbles initially allowing a single, then he fires at the stumps and his wayward throw ends up giving four overthrows, the Kolkata crowd loves it
exactly what Gambhir practised earlier in the over, leaving the ball outside off
length ball outside off, dabbed towards point by Gambhir, one of his most frequently used shots in one-daty cricket
short of length and on off stump, defended to the leg side
Junaid gets the ball to swerve away, Sehwag looks to drive that through the off but is beaten, not much footwork from Sehwag as usual
the men at cover point and cover aren't too far apart but Sehwag threads the gap there, opening the face to steer that to the point boundary for four
142kph from Junaid, short of length ball just outside off, Sehwag stays in the crease and jumps as he tries to get on top of the bounce, beaten
swerves in towards middle and leg, defended from the crease to the off side
pitched up this time, Sehwag mistimes as he looks to punch towards cover
a bouncer from Irfan, Gambhir was a bit late in ducking, but gets down in time
full and outside off, Gambhir gets well forward and drives but can't beat the man at cover
sprays that down the leg side

for the third time in his three overs Irfan is wondering whether he has a batsman bowled, Gambhir was initially moving forward then stayed in the crease as he defended with soft hands, so soft that the ball almost rolled back onto the stumps
short and down the leg side, another wide
a high full toss outside off as Irfan bowls from round the stumps, Sehwag misses out on that as he looks to force it through the off side
coming in towards the body, Sehwag looking to pull that away but it bounces far more than he expected, hit on the bat handle and the ball rolls down the pitch
another high full toss, well above knee height, slapped towards cover point

massive lbw lbw, Junaid v Sehwag is proving an enthralling battle here, it was the incutter from Junaid this time, Sehwag didn't read it, his bat was a long way away from the ball, struck high on the pads and that was going over, Sehwag survives
somehow Sehwag survives, Junaid at the top of his game here, induces another inside-edge, down towards fine leg for a single
Gambhir shuffles across and tucks a ball from middle towards fine leg
this time Junaid gets the ball to swerve away, Sehwag is half-drawn into playing at that one, withdraws the bat at the last moment, Junaid grins
too wide from Junaid, Sehwag shoulders arms
thick inside-edge onto the pads, a quick single is taken, India survive four overs of Junaid
Irfan proving a tricky customer once again, gets the ball to shoot up from back of a length, Sehwag looks to fend it away, hit on the bat handle before the ball rolls towards third man
the shot that has caused Gambhjir's downfall so often in recent times, a weak poke at a shortish ball outside off, beaten, he's has nicked through to the keeper or the slip cordon on plenty of times
much more confident from Gambhir, defended to the off side
another bouncer from Irfan, Gambhir gets inside the line of that one and ducks
full ball on the pads, helped down to fine leg by Gambhir
short of length ball, Sehwag drops it almost at his feet, there's some shouted discussion over whether to take a single, they decide against it
length ball just outside off, worked towards mid-on
short of length ball on off stump, moves in a hint, defended towards square leg
length ball played from the crease towards the off side
length ball just outside off, punched towards cover for a single

Junaid has been exceptional today, and here's his reward, this was perhaps not among his best deliveries, it was pitched up and wide, Gambhir looked to power that through the off side, inside-edges it onto the stumps
Kohli cautiously leaves the first ball, it was angling away from him outside off

short of length ball just outside off, Sehwag stands tall and defends towards backward point, Hafeez needed a direct hit there, Kohli was a goner, Hafeez misses, and for the second time in the innings there's four overthrows, again Eden Gardens is thrilled by that
gets that steepling bounce once more, Kohli gets behind the line and defends
pitched up, on middle stump, Kohli whips it towards midwicket for a couple
no footwork for Kohli as he flirts with one that was well outside off, beaten
sensational timing from Kohli, barely a push to send that speeding away behind backward point, not much wrong with the delivery either, back of a length and not too far outside off
solidly defended back towards the bowler
short and down the leg side, Sehwag ducks
short of length ball on off stump, Sehwag gets behind the line and defends, less of the exaggerated movement we saw for Junaid early on
pitched up, just around off stump, defended towards backward poin t
angling in from round the wicket, on the pads and that is clipped away towards deep square leg
back to over the wicket for Kohli, defended to the off side by Kohli
pitched up and just outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to that one

and again in the midst of a superb spell, Junaid strikes with an ordinary ball, it was heading down the leg side, Kohli could have let it go, instead he tickles it down the leg side, Kamran Akmal - the source of so many cricket jokes over the past few years - pulls off a stunner, diving to his left to pluck that one, started moving early to anticipate that one, the dangerous Kohli is gone
angling down the leg side, helped along towards fine leg by Sehwag
short of length ball outside off, defended to the leg side

a bouncer at 139.9kph, a wake-up call for Yuvraj, who first thought he could get on top of the bounce and defend and jumped up, but realised he couldn't and tries to duck and weave at the last moment, manages to evade the ball
solidly defended towards extra cover
nearly a wicket there, Yuvraj inside-edges just past the stumps and towards backward square leg
a bouncer to finish off the over, Sehwag spots it early, ducks and waits for it to fly over
seventh over for Junaid, given a chance against the new batsman Yuvraj, defended to the leg side
length ball on off stump, defended to the off side by Yuvraj, far less movement now for Junaid
length ball outside off, left alone by Yuvraj, that was 135kph
and once more Yuvraj doesn't have to play at it, gets the ball to shape away a little
short ball just outside off, Yuvraj drops his wrists and allows the ball through to the keeper

just inches wide of off stump, Kamran grins ruefully wondering how that misses the stumps, Junaid his hands on his head, it was the inducker after several going way, Yuvraj breavely shouldered arms, survives
slashed towards sweeper cover for a single
worked towards square leg for a single
nearly gone there, a sort of a leading edge almost sends the ball to mid-off, lands just short of the fielder, that's the wicket Pakistan needed
they have the wicket, Sehwag is struck in front of middle by a Gul delivery that moved in sharply, Sehwag is late with his stroke, an exuberant appeal from Gul, Bowden agrees and India are 59/3
length delivery , Raina moves across and defends towards cover
gets nicely behind the line and blocks it to the off side
pitched up and that is driven towards sweeper cover for a single
'Very well bowed, Hafeez," says Kamran, as Raina defends back to the bowler
more forward defence towards the bowler
more fielding for Hafeez as Raina taps it back
blocked to the off side by raina
tight over from Hafeez comes to an end, Raina skips down the track and pushes it to the right of the bowler
another inside-edge, Yuvraj survives as the ball squirts behind square leg
gets well on the back foot and guides the ball towards backward point

would have been a run-out if Gul had scored a direct hit, Raina drops the ball to his right and sets off, Gul was in his follow-through and sets off towards the ball, fields but can't get an accurate throw
clipped towards backward square leg for a single
short ball, 140kph, Raina's troubles against those are well-documented, takes his eyes off the ball and doesn't really duck as that whizzes past

another bouncer, Raina brings out the hook, that was pretty high, difficult to control, not sure Raina was completely at ease playing that, he connects well enough though and sends it behind square leg
spins on towards leg stump, defended to the leg side
length ball is carefully defended back to the bowler
Yuvraj living a streaky life here, goes for a full-blooded sweep, top edges it and that swirls over the keeper, giving slip a long chase
'Misbah,' screams Kamran as soon as Raina plays one off the back foot  towards cover, no run

slapped towards point, Yuvraj charges for a single, Raina took a couple of paces before shouting 'No, no, no, no,' immediately Kamran screams 'bowling end,' as he sees Yuvraj has a long way to go to get back, Yuvraj manages to beat the throw
defended to the off side
inside-edge as he looks to drive through the off side off the back foot, the ball rolls to the leg side
length ball just outside off, defended towards point
short ball is pulled towards deep square leg
length ball is pushed off the back foot towards cover

Yuvraj's struggles are over for this game, he was looking out of his depth there, the short ball from Gul, well outside off, Yuvraj goes for the pull, off the toed end of the bat and through to the keeper, Kamran accepts the straight forward chance, Yuvraj swings his bat in disgust before wlaking off
shortish and well outside off, easy leave for Dhoni
Hafeez keeping it on a length and around off, bowling from round the wicket, defended off the front foot
blocked to the leg side this time
length ball heading for off stump, tapped back to the bowler
slapped towards backward point for a single

back of a length ball outside off, Gul from round the wicket, clipped towards midwicket
sliding in towards the pads, helped down to fine leg for a single

another Gul bouncer, seemed to have take a bit of bat as Raina went for the pull, but the umpire has deemed that bouncer a wide, that ball just didn't come down, it kept rising and rising, even Kamran in this form had no chance to get to that, umpire deems it a wide
142kph just outside off, Raina sways away from the line of that short one and allows it through to the keeper
pitched up, and that is sent towards midwicket, immediately the call is for two, and they get it easily
Hafeez from over the wicket, defended towards midwicket
pushed to long-on for a single, a shot Dhoni plays  hell of a lot in the middle overs
on the pads, worked behind square leg
gets back in the crease and defends towards cover
length ball on middle and leg, worked in front of square leg

full ball from Irfan as he starts a new spell, squeezed down towards third man
pitched up and outside off, left alone
swerving away with the angle, left alone by Dhoni
much too wide to worry Dhoni
round the wicket and into the pads, clipped towards deep square leg
short of length ball just outside off, Irfan from over the wicket again, Raina helps it towards square leg for a single

flatter and on the pads, a rare loose delivery from Hafeez, glanced down to fine leg for four
back to a length and on off stump, no big turn here for Hafeez, just accurate
'good stop Hafeez,' says Kamran as Hafeez bends to his right to stop a Raina drive
blocked by Raina towards the bowler
appeal for lbw, that was going down the leg side afetr striking Raina low on the pads, Raina was looking to whip the ball towards the leg side but he missed

solid defense off the front foot to the leg side, not entirely sure why the crowd is suddenly making plenty of noise

Is Raina stumped? he looks tense as we wait for the third umpire's decision, he was out of the crease to try push the ball towards the off side, it was wide outside off, he misses and he can't balance himself properly, still tries to get his back leg in, but it is still in the air as the bails come off, India in a huge hole here
length ball on the stumps, worked towards midwicket
spins in sharply, defended to midwicket
worked off the back foot towards square leg
big lbw appeal, Ashwin might have been struck just outside off stump, everything else in place for an lbw
quicker, straighter one from Ajmal, blocked towards the bowler
pushed towards mid-on by Dhoni, Misbah has to rush across from midwicket to collect that
worked to midwicket by Dhoni
inside-edged towards deep backward square leg
punches a length ball towards mid-on
shortish ball just outside off, spins in a bit, defended off the back foot
turns in towards the pads, worked towards midwicket
shuffles across and works the ball to the leg side
opens the face to play the ball towards point, his favourite scoring area
pushed towards long-on for a single that brings up the Indian 100
slapped off the back foot towards point
moves across the stumps and glances the ball towards short fine leg
tough chance missed, that was a tossed up delivery from Ajmal, dipped on Ashwin, who got a thick outside edge, strikes Akmal on the pads

works it to backward square leg for a single
punched back towards the bowler
getting serious turn now, Ashwin skips down to a short of length ball and is struck on the pads

short from Ajmal, should have been put away, slapped towards extra cover where Irfan makes a diving stop
stays on the back foot and defends towards mid-on
moves away from the stumps and chops the ball against the spin towards cover

driven to extra cover by Ashwin

length ball is pushed towards mid-on
pitched up by Malik and that is defended back to the bowler

and another one bites the dust, can Shoaib Malik ever not make a contribution against India? Ashwin was charging down the ground and looking to thrash the ball through the off side, he misses the ball and is yards out as Akmal collects the ball and takes off the bails, only one result in this game now (apologies to SRJ fans)
slapped towards backward point
Malik from round the wicket, gets the ball to spin sharply away, leading edge past slip
defended by Jadeja and that ends a wicket maiden
length ball on middle and off, defended to the leg side
stays well back in the crease and whips it to the leg side

is it another stumping? Pakistan look like that they have got the big wicket here, no they haven't Dhoni survives, Dhoni stretches well forward to play that one but he looked to have a bit of his back leg behind the crease, and Kamran didn't collect the ball cleanly, though it ricocheted onto the stumps
short from Ajmal, spins in towards the pads, Dhone looks to whip it off the back foot, can't connect
bottom-edge sends the ball behind square leg

slapped towards deep point for a single
length ball on middle and leg stump, tucked towards midwicket

down to third man for a single
short of length and outside off, left alone

length ball outside off, defended towards cover
defended towards the bowler
on the pads, nurdled for a single to square leg
slapped towards square leg
length ball on the pads, worked towards midwicket for a couple
huge lbw appeal as Dhoni finally attempts a big hit, he misses and is hit on the pads, that was going down leg side
played off the back foot towards square leg
spinning in towards the batsman, cramping Dhoni for room, pushed back towards the bowler
clipped to square leg for a single

clipped towards deep square leg

spins in towards the pads, defended towards mid-on
a flighted delivery is sent towards backward point where a diving stop prevents the single
on the pads, clipped towards square leg
length ball, Jadeja looks to thump that over mid-on, can't get it high enough, an overhead catch for Junaid at mid-on who takes a leaping catch
doosra from Ajmal, defended to the off side

and Pakistan are two away from a famous victory, the magician Ajmal is too good for Bhuvneshwar, lbw, that drifts away and spins in catching Bhuveshwar on the crease, a bit of doubt whether that would have taken leg stump, but the umpire is satisfied
doosra again, spins away from Dinda, who defends from the crease to the off side
down the leg side for a wide
three in the over for Ajmal, India are nine down, local hero Dinda  is the latest to go, that pitched outside leg stump, but the Indian umpire is again convinced, he lifts the finger
Dhoni has finally decided to hit out, a length ball is launched towards the extra cover boundary

on the pads, clipped towards square leg, Dhoni declines the single

the doosra but Ishant keeps it out, defended to the off side
driven firmly towards extra cover
low full toss is punched to extra cover

thumped towards the man at long-on, a very tough chance for Shoaib Malik at the boundary, a diving attempt but he can't hold on, Dav Whatmore thinks that the winning catch and gets up in cleebration before sitting down calmly again
a yorker is squeezed out back to the bowler
a single taken towards mid-on
is that it? no it isn't, Ishant Sharma plays a low full toss into the ground and towards gully, Pakistan think they have the final wicket but they'll have to wait just a little longer
on the pads, Dhoni looks to glance it down the leg side
worked towards deep square leg, Dhoni sets off thinking he has time for two but then turns back on realising he doesn't
spins in towards the pads, clipped towards square leg

short of length and outside off, wafts at it and misses

careful defence from Ishant, towards cover

another bouncer, another wide, just 15 sixes needed now to tie the game
another Dhoni half-century, the man is un-outable in ODIs

what a delivery to finish it off, a ripping yorker takes out the off stump, Junaid screaming in joy, Pakistan take the series 2-0, they have been a cut above in this series, India had only two defeats in 24 home ODIs before Pakistan arrived, now they have two in two
